If not serving immediately, let cool completely, then replace covers with fresh waxed paper and foil and store in a cool, dry place, basting from time to time with rum or brandy, for up to 3 months. To serve, reheat by steaming 2 to 3 hours.', '4.4', 'https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/24227/christmas-plum-pudding/', '/Cuisine/European/UK and Ireland/English/', 'Total Fat 10g 13%, Saturated Fat 4g 18%, Cholesterol 32mg 11%, Sodium 69mg 3%, Total Carbohydrate 32g 12%, Dietary Fiber 3g 10%, Total Sugars 15g, Protein 4g, Vitamin C 6mg 31%, Calcium 50mg 4%, Iron 1mg 7%, Potassium 201mg 4%', 'Prep Time: 30 mins, Cook Time: 5 hrs, Total Time: 5 hrs 30 mins, Servings: 20, Yield: 20 servings', 'https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/woAJkvTH-kBbiEjtT7Xx5ojv3d4=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/4621630-f60cdb1af9c44d00b0598542639f3971.jpg');
In a 2 quart baking dish, stir together plums, 1 cup sugar, water, tapioca and cinnamon. Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes. (You can also cook the plum mixture in the microwave for 15 minutes.)
Raise oven temperature to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).
